AT THE REQUEST OF:
West Point Towne Center Community Association
4645 East Cotton Gin Loop
Phoenix, AZ 85040
(602) 437-4777
2ºDocument
51
mo
NOTICE AND CLAIM OF LIEN
Jodi Phelps, being first and duly sworn, deposes and says as follows:
1. That she/he is an authorized agent of West Point Towne Center Community Association, an Arizona Corporation, being a Homeowner's
Association organized to own, operate and manage the commonly held facilities of West Point Towne Center Community Association.
2. That the Declaration of Covenants, Conditions and Restrictions are a covenant running with and binding the land in said subdivision; that the
Covenants, Conditions and Restrictions impose annual assessment on individual parcels of property within said subdivision and create a lien of
assessment in order to collect delinquent assessments; the assessment is both a lien against the real property and the personal obligation of the
record owner or purchaser of said real property.
3. Upon information and belief, the record owner or purchaser of Account #KB 162 is Derik Thibodeau and Brianna Thibodeau, the following
real property situated in the county of Maricopa, State of Arizona:
Lot 162, KAUFMAN BROAD AT WEST POINT, according to the plat of record in the office of the County Recorder of
Maricopa County, Arizona, in Book 445 of Maps, Page 47
4. That the assessments on said real property are delinquent in the amount of $440.00, being due and presently unpaid.
5. The lien claimed against Lot # 162 is of a continuing nature and the amount stated as due and owing in Paragraph 4 will increase, and
continue to increase, if Owner(s) continues nonpayment of assessments in the future. The increases will be comprised of future unpaid
assessments, late fees, interest, costs of collection, other amounts as authorized under the Declaration and, if applicable, attomeys' fees.
6. This claim of lien is being made pursuant to the Declaration and is being recorded to inform the public of the current amount of said lien, and
is not a waiver of any prior lien on Lot # 162, which pursuant to the Declaration existed before the recording of this notice. A copy of this lien is
being sent to the Owners at their last known mailing address(es).
7. This is an attempt to collect a debt and any information obtained can be used for that purpose.
IN WITNESS HEREOF, I have hereunto set my hand this 30th day of June 2022.
AZELDP-80164
STATE OF ARIZONA )
) ss.
COUNTY OF MARICOPA )
SUBSCRIBED AND SWORN to before me on this 30th day of June 2022, by Jodi Phelps.
My commission expires:
Notary Public
CHARLOTTE THERRIEN
Notary Public - State of Arizona
MARICOPA COUNTY
Commission # 585543
Expires June 27, 2024
